When using with upsert inc is updating the count by twice both times when it is insert or when it is update.

Code to reproduce

{code:scala}
def upsertUser(user: User): Future[User] = {

    val combineAll = Updates.combine (
      set("name", user.name),
      inc("timesLoggedIn", 1),
      setOnInsert("firstLogin", new Date()),
      set("lastLogin", new Date())
    )

    val upsertObservable: Observable[result.UpdateResult] = usersCollection.updateOne(Filters.eq("sAMAccountName", user.sAMAccountName), combineAll, UpdateOptions().upsert(true))

    upsertObservable.subscribe(new Observer[result.UpdateResult] {
      override def onNext(results: result.UpdateResult): Unit = logger.info(s"Successfully completed user upsert => $results")
      override def onError(e: Throwable): Unit = logger.error(s"Error in user upsert => $e")
      override def onComplete(): Unit = {}
    })

    upsertObservable.toFuture() map {results => user }
  }
{code}

This is a similar issue to JAVA-2105, where {{$explain}} modifier is ignored when connecting to 3.2 server. 

Below code snippet returns the query plan when connected to v3.0.x, but returns the first document when connected to v3.2. Tested on MongoDB v3.2.5 using driver v1.1.0 and Scala v2.11.7.

{code}
collection.find().modifiers(Document("$explain"->true)).first().printResults()
{code}

A work around for this is to use runCommand to get the query plan.

{code}
db.runCommand(Document("explain"->Document("find"->"collection"))).printResults()
{code}

